---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
import { url } from '../utils/url';
---

<ContentLayout title="About This Project" description="About the KubeCon 2026 Virtual Power Plants presentation and educational website.">

<h1>About This Project</h1>

<p class="text-xl" style="color: var(--color-text-muted); max-width: 600px;">
  An open-source educational resource about Virtual Power Plants and the future of the
  electricity grid.
</p>

<hr />

<h2 id="what-this-is">What This Is</h2>

<p>
  This website accompanies a KubeCon 2026 presentation about Virtual Power Plants — how
  distributed energy resources like solar panels, home batteries, and heat pumps can be
  coordinated by software to stabilize the electricity grid.
</p>

<p>
  The presentation and this site were built to make grid technology accessible to a broad
  audience. You do not need an engineering degree to understand how the grid works, why it
  is changing, or what Virtual Power Plants do. We wrote everything for readers aged 12 and up.
</p>

<h2 id="who-built-this">Who Built This</h2>

<p>
  This project was built by <strong>Mario Olivio Flores</strong> and <strong>LeRenzo Tolbert-Malcolm</strong>,
  engineers at <a href="https://enpal.de" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Enpal</a>.
  Enpal is a German energy company that installs solar panels, batteries, and heat pumps in
  homes across Europe — the same hardware that powers Virtual Power Plants.
</p>

<h2 id="open-source">Open Source</h2>

<p>
  All research behind this project is open source and fact-checked. Every claim on the learning
  pages links back to primary sources in our research library. If you find an error, please
  open an issue.
</p>

<p>
  The source code is available on GitHub:<br />
  <a href="https://github.com/marioflores/kubecon-2026-vpp" class="font-mono text-sm" style="color: var(--color-primary);">
    github.com/marioflores/kubecon-2026-vpp
  </a>
</p>

<h2 id="built-with">Built With</h2>

<p>
  This site is built with <a href="https://astro.build" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Astro</a>,
  <a href="https://react.dev" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary);">React</a>, and
  <a href="https://tailwindcss.com" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary);">TailwindCSS</a>.
  The presentation itself uses React with
  <a href="https://formidable.com/open-source/spectacle/" class="hover:underline" style="color: var(--color-primary);">Spectacle</a>.
</p>

<div class="my-8 p-6 rounded-lg" style="background: rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.04); border: 1px solid rgba(34, 211, 238, 0.15);">
  <div class="font-mono text-sm mb-2" style="color: var(--color-primary); letter-spacing: 0.08em;">EXPLORE</div>
  <a href={url("/research")} class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">
    Research Library
  </a>
  <div class="text-sm mt-1" style="color: var(--color-text-dim);">
    Sources, data, and references behind every claim on this site.
  </div>
</div>

</ContentLayout>
